  "context": "Gas prices climbing as Strait of Hormuz effectively closed to tanker traffic (Day 11). AAA national average at $3.54/gal (up 36 cents from pre-war $3.18). Brent crude at $112.98/barrel, WTI at $101.97. Pump prices lag crude by 1-2 weeks — analysts project $4+/gal within days. California highest at $5.20/gal. Diesel at $4.66/gal. Biggest weekly gain in crude futures history. GasBuddy's Patrick De Haan expects prices to continue climbing, while Eurasia Group's Ian Bremmer expects $4/gal next week."
